# QR

With the QR module, users can generate QR codes with or without an image. Response will be always in base64 format.

Base URL:

```
https://api.everrest.educata.dev/qrcode
```

## Sample

- Method: `GET`
- URL: `https://api.everrest.dev/qrcode`

### Example

```sh
curl -X 'GET' \
  'https://api.everrest.educata.dev/qrcode' \
  -H 'accept: application/json'
```

### Response

```
data:image/png;base64,
```

<img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="sample response image">

## Generate

- Method: `POST`
- URL: `https://api.everrest.dev/qrcode/generate`

### Body

- `text`: string

### Example

```sh
curl -X 'POST' \
  'https://api.everrest.educata.dev/qrcode/generate' \
  -H 'accept: application/json' \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d '{
  "text": "if you liked the project, you can star it at: https://github.com/educata/everrest"
}'
```

### Response

```
data:image/png;base64,
```

<img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="generated image">

## Generate with image

- Method: `POST`
- URL: `https://api.everrest.dev/qrcode/generate_with_image`

### Body

- `text`: string
- `imageURL`: string

### Example

```sh
curl -X 'POST' \
  'https://api.everrest.educata.dev/qrcode/generate_with_image' \
  -H 'accept: application/json' \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d '{
  "text": "With this QR module, users can generate QR codes with or without an image. Response will be always in base64 format.",
  "imageURL": "https://everrest.educata.dev/logo.png"
}'
```

### Response

```
data:image/png;base64,
```

<img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="sample generated image">
